rt-sort.pl is a script for sorting your rtorrent-downloads based on name an watch-dir like:

for TV-series: 'downloads/Serier/HD/Show/Sesong 1/show.S01E01.720p.HDTV.×264-OK'
Movies: 'downloads/Filmer/HD/Movie.2011.720p.BluRay.×264-OK'

add this to your .rtorrent.rc:

# rt-sort START
# Watch dirs
schedule = watch_directory_2,10,10,"load_start=~/torrents/Filmer/*.torrent,d.set_custom2=FILM"
schedule = watch_directory_3,10,10,"load_start=~/torrents/Serier/*.torrent,d.set_custom2=SERIE"

# On finnished
system.method.set_key = event.download.finished,move_me,“d.set_directory=\”$execute_capture=~/scripts/myscripts/rt-sort.pl,$d.get_base_path=,$d.get_custom2=\""

# END

edit the lines to fit you.

move .rt-sort.cfg to youre home folder (~/) and edit it to fit you.
